       /bin/format  [-qvVE]  [-f first] [-l last] [-i interleave]
       device[t]

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       The format command formats floppy disks.  Unless otherwise
       specified,  formatting  starts  at  track  0 and continues
       until an error is returned at the end of a partition.

   CCoommmmaanndd ooppttiioonnss
       The -f and -l options specify the first and last track  to
       be formatted.  The default interleave of 1 may be modified
       by using the -i option.  device must specify a raw  (char-
       acter)  floppy  device.   The t indicates the entire disk.
       Absence of this letter indicates that the first  track  of
       the diskette cannot be accessed.  Quiet mode.  Perform the
       floppy disk format operation, but do  not  report  status,
       inquiry,  or  error messages.  Verbose mode (always true).
       Verify.  After tracks are formatted, a  random  sector  is
       chosen and a write of test data is done into it.  The sec-
       tor is then read back and a comparison is  made.   exhaus-
       tive  verify.  Every sector is verified by write/read/com-
       pare.

FFiilleess
       /dev/rdsk/*     raw device for partition to be formatted

